{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"author":"Aniruddha Mysore"}},"portfolio":{"edges":[{"node":{"html":"<h1>About</h1>\n<p>I am a student pursuing an undergraduate degree in PESIT Bangalore, majoring in Computer Science and Engineering.</p>","frontmatter":{"section":"About"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>Work</h1>\n<p>I have previously worked at Reap Benefit and Paisool (INBE)</p>","frontmatter":{"section":"Work"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>Research</h1>\n<h2>Semantic Segmentation of Eyes Regions</h2>\n<p>Developed a segmentation model for the Open Eye Dataset released by Facebook, under the guidance of Prof\nGowri Srinivasa. Our CNN model achieved a better mIoU score than the baseline submission by the Facebook\nOpenEDS team. The paper has been submitted to CVPR 2020.</p>\n<h2>Evaluating Trends in Software Development in Open-Source projects</h2>\n<p>Presently working on analyzing the software development metrics of open source projects under the guidance\nof Prof Subhajt Datta, Singapore University of Technology and Desig</p>\n<h2>Re-establishing communication in disaster-struck areas with drones</h2>\n<p>Ideated and demonstrated a drone network to set up communication channels in the aftermath of a natural\ndisaster. Our project was a finalist at IEEE CCEM Student PoC and presented at the IEEE Drone Conference\n2018.</p>","frontmatter":{"section":"Research"}}}]},"projects":{"edges":[{"node":{"html":"<p>Worked with some wonderful people like Harshika Jain to develop the Hyperloop India Pod telemetry software.</p>","id":"7bc1b6ad-1502-52ad-84d3-035015b0a4fc","headings":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Hyperloop Pod Telmetry","type":"project","section":null,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/c19c3fe4f5950c2c6c5f5311edfa0749/a3fa0/hype.png","srcSet":"/static/c19c3fe4f5950c2c6c5f5311edfa0749/e7c66/hype.png 200w,\n/static/c19c3fe4f5950c2c6c5f5311edfa0749/140ea/hype.png 400w,\n/static/c19c3fe4f5950c2c6c5f5311edfa0749/a3fa0/hype.png 800w,\n/static/c19c3fe4f5950c2c6c5f5311edfa0749/054e8/hype.png 831w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"parent":{"__typename":"File","id":"95e134e1-4c90-5b47-b45c-410e498a2e64"}}},{"node":{"html":"<p>Reinforcement Learning agent that plays on the Pokemon Showdown simmulator.</p>","id":"f51850c4-0b2c-54c1-aaaa-776367297468","headings":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Pokemon Showdown Bot","type":"project","section":null,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.0052910052910053,"src":"/static/80bb2fe8da5758f253e669069c41ee17/77b45/poke.png","srcSet":"/static/80bb2fe8da5758f253e669069c41ee17/e7c66/poke.png 200w,\n/static/80bb2fe8da5758f253e669069c41ee17/140ea/poke.png 400w,\n/static/80bb2fe8da5758f253e669069c41ee17/77b45/poke.png 760w","sizes":"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px"}}}},"parent":{"__typename":"File","id":"abdd622f-69a0-50e6-8863-70ba8468fa2d"}}},{"node":{"html":"<p>A series of semi-successful projects on using drones for immediate communication and response during disasters.</p>","id":"362cc17b-ecd2-5e95-9049-e8af27758ef1","headings":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Drones for Disaster Response","type":"project","section":null,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/b2da9c100c09ea257b6c941844339651/b9460/drone.png","srcSet":"/static/b2da9c100c09ea257b6c941844339651/e7c66/drone.png 200w,\n/static/b2da9c100c09ea257b6c941844339651/b9460/drone.png 378w","sizes":"(max-width: 378px) 100vw, 378px"}}}},"parent":{"__typename":"File","id":"f7532739-50ad-5c88-b3a9-4de763230920"}}}]}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":true}}